			<h2>Correspondence</h2>
			<a class="xsmall link-alt" href="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor">Write a Letter to the Editor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>
		</div>

		<div id="article-correspondences" class="correspondences correspondences-collapsed">
								<div class="block-correspondence" id="1448">
		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p>I wept as I read Ann Bauer&rsquo;s essay &ldquo;<a href="/article/53">Father and Son</a>&rdquo; [February 2007]. I recently ended a relationship with someone who might meet the diagnostic criteria for several personality disorders, but each day I still struggle with what Bauer described so well: &ldquo;Though it [autism] may prevent someone .&nbsp;.&nbsp;. from interacting freely with the world at large, if you are lucky enough to make contact with such a person &mdash; to catch a glimpse of the furtive, naked soul ill-clad in a human body &mdash; you never want to let go.&rdquo; I&rsquo;m still learning to put my own emotional well-being first. Sometimes letting go is the best choice.</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">Name Withheld<br></p>
					</blockquote>
	</div>

					</div>

